03/06/2004
THE HAGUE, Netherlands -- The Dutch Parliament may soon adopt a resolution supporting Macedonia's accession to NATO by 2007 at the latest. 
Macedonian Defence Minister Vlado Buckovski met on Wednesday (2 June) with the chairwoman of parliament's committee on defence and security, Nebahat Albayrak. 
In a subsequent meeting with Dutch counterpart Henk Kamp, Buckovski was assured The Netherlands would assist Macedonia in its NATO preparation efforts. 
Buckovski in turn said Macedonia might send peacekeepers to BiH next year as part of its participation in the Southeast Europe Multinational Brigade. 
(MIA, A1 TV - 02/06/04)
